author: Inside Edition
description: Thousands of Americans find themselves stuck across the Caribbean following the fallout from the US raid in Venezuela. Hundreds of flights have been cancelled. Cameron Buttrick, who lives in New York, and her dad Brian, are trying to get back to the US from the island of Curacao. They spoke with Inside Edition's Alison Hall. American Airlines said it added 7,000 extra seats to try to ease the backlog. Delta added 2,600. United and Southwest said they are also working on adding more flights.
title: Thousands Of Americans Stuck Across Caribbean

author: Inside Edition
description: Captured Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro and his wife, Cilia Flores, headed to their first court appearance in New York surrounded by heavily armed federal agents. Security is tense at the lower Manhattan courthouse, where protestors have gathered demanding Maduro be released. Maduro's arrest has left a power vacuum in Venezuela. President Donald Trump says the new leader must co-operate with his administration.
title: Captured Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro Appears in NYC Court

author: Inside Edition
description: More details have been released about the raid that brought Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro and his wife Cilia Flores to the United States in handcuffs. John McPhee is a former Delta Force soldier, the elite unit that carried out the raid, and he spoke with Inside Edition. The Delta Force team reached Caracas at 1 a.m. ET on Saturday morning and the operation was over at 3:30 am. An hour later, Maduro arrived in New York. Thirty-two Cubans were killed in the air strikes.
title: New Details About Raid That Captured Nicolas Maduro

author: Inside Edition
description: Michelle Newton spent her first holiday season with her long-lost father, Joe, and the extended family she never knew, all 70 of them. Six weeks ago, Michelle's mother Debra was arrested after 42 years on the run for allegedly abducting her at the age of three. Authorities came to Debra's house at The Villages retirement community outside Orlando, Florida. Michelle tells Inside Edition police told her she wasn't who she thought she was. Her father, now 67, never stopped looking for her.
title: Woman Reunites With Long Lost Family 42 Years Later

author: Inside Edition
description: In 2025, Brian Joseph King says he was hired to go on tour with Smith and his band. King says after he made allegations of sexual harassment to Smith's management team, he was fired. Smith's attorney fired back calling the allegations "false, baseless and reckless."
title: Violinist Makes Accusations Against Will Smith #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A man was stuck inside a burning car and the responding officer was desperate to free him. It happened in Cortland, Ohio. Police say the car crashed through a fence, flipped, and caught fire. When the occupant was located, he notified the office that he was injured, possibly with a broken leg. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Cops Rescue Injured Driver After Car Flips And Catches Fire

author: Inside Edition
description: A bald eagle is under close watch after it was discovered in a pig pen in Gila, New Mexico. According to Gila Wildlife Rescue, the bird is battered and bruised and is getting tested for West Nile virus, avian influenza, and lead poisoning. In California, another eagle is healing after it was electrocuted. The eagle is dealing with several injuries, including a broken coracoid, a bone that connects a bird’s shoulder to its keel to enable flight. Inside Edition Digital has more.
title: 2 Bald Eagles, One Electrocuted, One Found In A Pig Pen, Hoping To Recover

author: Inside Edition
description: First responder Dena Suihkonen from Minnesota was severely injured in an accident involving a dunk tank.
title: Woman Paralyzed After Dunk Tank Malfunction #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Two years ago, doctors were not sure Morrie Covin would survive after a freak accident at her grandparents' house in Alabama.
title: 6-Year-Old Stands For First Time Since Freak Accident #shorts
